SIMPLE: superscription
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Superscription
<hw>Su`per*scrip"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>superscriptio</ets>. See <er>Superscribe</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of superscribing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is written or engraved on the surface,
outside, or above something else; specifically, an address on a letter,
envelope, or the like.</def> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>superscription</qex> of his accusation was written over,
The King of the Jews.</q> <rj><qau>Mark xv. 26.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Pharm.)</fld> <def>That part of a prescription
which contains the Latin word <xex>recipe</xex> (Take) or the sign
<?/.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supersecular</ent>⟦br⟧
